# AI curation workflow -- STUB, INTENTIONALLY DISABLED.
#
# This file ends in `.disabled` so GitHub Actions does not run it. It is a
# placeholder for a future step that would turn the deterministic raw
# extraction (paths, beta flags, contexts) into curated, human-readable spec
# prose -- e.g. drafting `.http` sections or SUMMARY narrative from the raw
# literals.
#
# It is NOT implemented on purpose. The deterministic pipeline
# (fetch -> extract -> compare -> validate) must remain the source of truth and
# must never depend on a model's output to decide what is published. Any AI step
# added here must:
#   - run only after `scripts/validate-extraction.sh` has passed,
#   - treat raw/*.txt as read-only ground truth,
#   - never relax the FLAGGED.md / unreleased-codename gate,
#   - open a clearly-labeled PR for human review, adding no secrets beyond an
#     explicitly configured, least-privilege token.
#
# To enable later: implement the job, rename to `ai-curation.yml`, and document
# the model/token requirements in CONTRIBUTING.md first.
